        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks CD for reading his MS [<hi rend="doubleUnderline">8412</hi>] and for his suggestions.</p> 
            <p>Clarifies his statement on the contraction of the bud-axis: did not mean to imply that this contraction occurred in an individual’s life-time, rather that it was the effect, after the course of ages, of successive favourable modifications.</p>
            <p>Believes the true theory of phyllotaxy will give a convincing illustration and proof of the theory of evolution.</p>
        </abstract>
